<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 1:17PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern McCone
and western Dawson Counties through 215 PM MDT...
At 116 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles north of Circle, moving northeast at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Vida.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
